Enhance the cybersecurity at your home.

To improve cybersecurity at my home, I made a few simple but important changes to keep my devices and personal data safe.

First, I updated my Wi-Fi password and made it stronger, and I also changed the default login details of my router.
I enabled multi-factor authentication on important accounts like my email and banking apps so that even if someone gets my password, 
they still can’t access my accounts.

I also made sure my laptop and phone are always updated, because updates fix security issues that hackers can exploit. Along with that,
I use antivirus software and keep my firewall turned on for extra protection.

Another thing I did was create a separate guest network for devices like my smart TV and other IoT devices. This helps reduce the 
risk of someone accessing my main network. I’ve also become more careful about clicking on links or emails that look suspicious.

Overall, these small steps have made me more aware of cybersecurity and helped me better protect my personal information at home.
